# Design System — Lumière / Ombre Split

## Core Concept
The UI is split vertically: LEFT = Lumière (light), RIGHT = Ombre (dark).
Hovering one side expands it to ~65% with a spring animation. The other compresses.
Reference: norgram.co — essential, barely-there, Swiss Design meets editorial.

## Layout Rules
- Full viewport height, no scroll on the outer container
- Each panel scrolls internally (overflow-y: auto, custom thin scrollbar)
- Panel transition: `transition: flex 0.6s cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)`
- Header: fixed top, 48px height, spans full width, translucent bg
- No visible borders between panels — use the color contrast itself
- Center divider: 2px line, opacity 0.1, or no line at all

## Color Tokens
```
--lumiere-bg: #f4f4f4
--lumiere-fg: #0c0c0c
--lumiere-muted: #6b6b6b
--lumiere-accent: #3d6b4a     (muted green — positive)
--lumiere-accent-light: #e8f0ea

--ombre-bg: #0a0a0a
--ombre-fg: #e5e5e5
--ombre-muted: #6b6b6b
--ombre-accent: #7a5163       (muted rose — negative)
--ombre-accent-light: #1a1218

--neutre: #5c5c5c
--border-light: rgba(0,0,0,0.06)
--border-dark: rgba(255,255,255,0.06)
```

## Typography
- Font: `Inter` (import from Google Fonts or next/font)
- Base size: 13px
- Line height: 1.5
- Headings: 600 weight, no uppercase
- Labels: 11px, uppercase, letter-spacing 0.05em, muted color
- Numbers: `font-variant-numeric: tabular-nums; font-feature-settings: "tnum"`
- Hero stats: 48px, 500 weight, tracking tight

## Component Style Rules
- No shadows — use subtle borders or bg differences
- No border-radius > 4px (prefer 2px or 0)
- Cards: 1px border, no shadow, slight bg offset
- Buttons: ghost style, no fill, border on hover
- Charts: no gridlines, minimal axis labels, area fills at 0.15 opacity
- Map: CARTO Positron (light panel), CARTO Dark Matter (dark panel)
- Icons: Lucide, 16px default, 1.5px stroke
- Spacing: 4px base grid (p-1 = 4px, p-2 = 8px, etc.)

## Animation Rules
- All transitions use `cubic-bezier(0.16, 1, 0.3, 1)` (spring)
- Duration: 300-600ms for layout, 150ms for hover states
- New events: fade in + translateY(8px)
- Numbers: count-up on mount (use requestAnimationFrame)
- Map markers: subtle pulse on new events (CSS @keyframes)
- Respect `prefers-reduced-motion: reduce`

## Responsive
- Desktop (>1024px): side-by-side split
- Tablet (768-1024px): same split but panels narrower
- Mobile (<768px): tab switch (Lumière / Ombre tabs) instead of split

## What NOT to do
- No gradients (except very subtle ones on charts)
- No colored backgrounds on cards
- No bold colors except the two accents (green, rose)
- No more than 2 font weights per panel
- No decorative elements — every pixel must convey information
- No loading spinners — use skeleton screens with subtle pulse
- No toast notifications — use inline status indicators
